{"id": "duc04-testb-45:6#19", "contents": "The American ambassador in Kenya, Prudence Bushnell, had earlier recommended that the embassy be moved to a safer location, but her advice was rejected. Furthermore, an Egyptian believed to have been directly involved in the bombings outlined the Kenya plot to American intelligence officials last November. Mustafa Mahmoud Said Ahmed's account was so specific \u2013 he said terrorists were planning to detonate a truck bomb in the embassy's underground garage \u2013 that it called for more than a temporary increase in security. However, it was discounted, even thought to be a ruse to lure the embassy into new security measures that terrorists could monitor and defeat."}
